TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
$a=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);
$b=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);
$c=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);

BEGIN_TEXT

$PAR
The following three points are given in polar coordinates.  What are the Cartesian coordinates of each point?

$PAR$HR$PAR
(a) \((2,2\pi/3)\)

$PAR
\(x =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

$PAR
\(y =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

$PAR$HR$PAR
(b) \((4,3\pi)\)

$PAR
\(x =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

$PAR
\(y =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

$PAR$HR$PAR
(c) \((-2,-5\pi/6)\)

$PAR
\(x =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

$PAR
\(y =\)  \{ans_rule(30)\}

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp("-1"));
ANS(num_cmp("sqrt(3)"));
ANS(num_cmp("-4"));
ANS(num_cmp("0"));
ANS(num_cmp("sqrt(3)"));
ANS(num_cmp("1"));

